Final Program

Saturday September 5, 2015
8:00-8:45 Registration
8:45-9:00 Opening: Paolo Tonella, Marcio Barros, Yvan Labiche
9:00-10:30 Research Track Session #1: Software Construction (Session Chair: Andrea Arcuri)

  • Shin Yoo, Amortised Optimisation of Non-Functional Property in Production Environment (slides)
  • Chris Simons, David White and Jeremy Singer, Search-based Refactoring: Metrics are Not Enough (slides)
  • Jose Manuel Calderon Trilla, Simon Poulding and Colin Runciman, Weaving Parallel Threads: Searching for Useful Parallelism in Functional Programs (slides)
10:30-11:00 Coffee break
11:00-12:30 Challenge Track Session #1: Search Based Software Testing (Session Chair: Shin Yoo)

  • Yi Bian, Serkan Kirbas, Mark Harman, Yue Jia and Zheng Li, Regression Test Case Prioritisation for Guava (slides)
  • José Campos, Gordon Fraser, Andrea Arcuri and Rui Abreu, Continuous Test Generation on Guava (slides)
  • Ermira Daka, José Campos, Jonathan Dorn, Gordon Fraser and Westley Weimer, Generating Readable Unit Tests for Guava (slides)
  • Justyna Petke, Testing Django Configurations Using Combinatorial Interaction Testing (slides)
12:30-14:00 Lunch
14:00-15:30 Research Track Session #2: Software Verification (Session Chair: Myra Cohen)

  • Markus Wagner, Mahmoud Bokhari and Thorsten Bormer, An improved Beam-Search for Testing Formal Verification Systems
  • José Miguel Rojas, José Campos, Mattia Vivanti, Gordon Fraser and Andrea Arcuri, Combining Multiple Coverage Criteria in Search-Based Unit Test Generation (slides)
  • Fang Yuan, Yi Bian, Zheng Li and Ruilian Zhao, Epistatic Genetic Algorithm for Test Case Prioritization (slides)
15:30-16:00 Coffee break
16:00-17:30 Challenge Track Session #2: Genetic Programming and Improvement (Session Chair: Jerffeson de Souza)

  • Andrea Mattavelli, Alberto Goffi and Alessandra Gorla, Synthesis of Equivalent Method Calls in Guava (slides)
  • Nathan Burles, Edward Bowles, Alexander E. I. Brownlee, Zoltan A. Kocsis, Jerry Swan and Nadarajen Veerapen, Object-Oriented Genetic Improvement for Improved Energy Consumption in Google Guava (slides)
  • Alexandru Marginean, Earl Barr, Mark Harman and Yue Jia, Automated Transplantation of Call Graph and Layout Features into Kate (slides)
  • Yue Jia, Mark Harman, William B. Langdon and Alexandru Marginean, Grow and Serve: Growing Django Citation Services Using SBSE (slides)
  • Nathan Burles, Edward Bowles, Bobby R. Bruce and Komsan Srivisut, Specialising Guava’s Cache to Reduce Energy Consumption (slides)
17:30-18:00 SSBSE Steering Committee election
19:30-21:30 Reception [Foyer Centro Congressi]
Sunday September 6, 2015
9:00-10:30 Keynote speaker #1: Prof. Kenneth De Jong, Co-evolutionary Algorithms: A Useful Computational Abstraction? (slides)
10:30-11:00 Coffee break

14:00-15:30 Research Track Session #3: Theoretical SBSE (Session Chair: Yuanyuan Zhang)
